#: ../../source/example_gallery/distributed.rst:2
#: 3709721b974446bfa68ac67011093368
msgid "Distributed FEM"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/distributed.rst:4
#: 31a0d16cf35a4f09a8e8297148686308
msgid ""
"Three scripts in ``examples/distributed/`` cover the building blocks for "
"multi-GPU FEM in TensorMesh: graph coloring on the element adjacency "
"graph, spectral domain decomposition, and a single-GPU-vs-multi-GPU "
"assembly benchmark on a structured tetrahedral cube."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/distributed.rst:12
#: 41c4e4a73ff44fc08f81d117600b707b
msgid ""
"The distributed layer is a research-grade path. It works, the benchmarks "
"are real, but the public API is still settling — the "
":doc:`../user_guide/index` deliberately does not document it as a first-"
"class workflow yet. Treat the examples below as recipes to learn from, "
"not as a stable interface."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/distributed.rst:20
#: 893a76fa9e8145959219c80a816e1a85
msgid "Element-graph coloring — ``graph_coloring.py``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/distributed.rst:22
#: 3a2a50e8700f4462b06ec6c62d347261
msgid ""
"Race-free atomic-add assembly on GPU needs a coloring of the element-"
"adjacency graph: elements that touch a common DOF must not share a color,"
" so each color class can be scattered into the global matrix in parallel."
" ``mesh.color()`` does this in one call, running a parallel Welsh-Powell-"
"style heuristic on the GPU when available:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/distributed.rst:29
#: 44e7529fb0144859b877e7b2107b1a21
msgid "examples/distributed/graph_coloring.py (essence)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/distributed.rst:41
#: 14e7f11c51b443f1b28702885448c895
msgid ""
"For a regular triangulation of the unit square the algorithm typically "
"finds 6–8 colors — close to the optimal chromatic number for a 2D "
"triangle adjacency graph. The visualization paints each element by its "
"color class, which gives the familiar striped / banded pattern."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/distributed.rst:47
#: 83efa13ddb614253ba8c751c2a05984c
msgid "Triangular element coloring with 7 color classes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/distributed.rst:52
#: 1a212316dfdf4f84bf441ea41df321e5
msgid ""
"``graph_coloring.py`` output: a triangular mesh of the unit square "
"painted by element color class. The Welsh-Powell heuristic finds 7 colors"
" here; elements sharing a color never share a node, so each color class "
"can be assembled in parallel without write conflicts."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/distributed.rst:60
#: f4bc5453189b46b18e6720fc64b3d2d3
msgid "Spectral domain decomposition — ``graph_partition.py``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/distributed.rst:62
#: 6b7327f0df0b4710ad72ad30a39e1809
msgid ""
"For multi-GPU work the mesh has to be split into ``n_parts`` balanced "
"subdomains with small interfaces. ``partition_mesh`` with "
"``method=\"spectral\"`` computes the Fiedler vector of the graph "
"Laplacian and recursively bisects:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/distributed.rst:67
#: bbeba8997af9463aa9f66ab94537a54b
msgid "examples/distributed/graph_partition.py (essence)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/distributed.rst:74
#: 580f54ab24d5400cbca968be2dc9c414
msgid ""
"The returned list of :class:`~tensormesh.Mesh` objects each carries "
"**ghost nodes** — the boundary nodes that belong to two subdomains get "
"duplicated, with their original global IDs stored in "
"``submesh.point_data[\"orig_nid\"]``. The script's exploded-view "
"visualization separates the four subdomains in space and circles the "
"shared interface nodes — the geometric picture you usually have to draw "
"on a whiteboard to explain a domain decomposition."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/distributed.rst:82
#: 43f8be13eeed47208143becfa95cb3d5
msgid "4-way domain decomposition with ghost nodes (exploded view)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/distributed.rst:87
#: 91b79c740d4f459599347948ea0116c9
msgid ""
"``graph_partition.py`` output: a 4-way spectral partition of the unit "
"square in exploded view. Each subdomain is rendered in its own color; the"
" highlighted dots along each subdomain's shared boundary are the **ghost "
"nodes** — duplicated copies of the interface vertices that each rank owns"
" locally, with the original global IDs preserved in "
"``submesh.point_data[\"orig_nid\"]``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/distributed.rst:97
#: 475d99f52f37422d83875c5c1d9a5259
msgid "Multi-GPU assembly benchmark — ``benchmark_assembly.py``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/distributed.rst:99
#: f7ad8bf9c6d74017a799a2fe47d0c048
msgid ""
"The headline distributed-FEM benchmark. A structured tetrahedral cube of "
"size :math:`(n+1)^3` points and :math:`5 n^3` tets is assembled (i) on a "
"single GPU, (ii) across all visible GPUs via ``torch.multiprocessing``. "
"The driver sweeps :math:`n` from a configurable starting size until "
"either path runs out of memory."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/distributed.rst:105
#: 7f1bc7b498714ae490e4ce0c23021a45
msgid ""
"The interesting machinery lives in "
":class:`~tensormesh.distributed.DistributedMesh`, which wraps the "
"spectral partition + per-subdomain ghost-node bookkeeping into a single "
"object:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/distributed.rst:110
#: e0920cb0d1174704a6aeeea55dda2577
msgid "examples/distributed/benchmark_assembly.py (essence)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/distributed.rst:136
#: a8b4597b77da40d69702695ab6a8af98
msgid "A few details that matter:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/distributed.rst:138
#: 89fcea77e3ad47beb652bbeec95bec38
msgid ""
"**One process per GPU.** ``torch.multiprocessing`` with "
"``set_start_method(\"spawn\")`` gives each process its own Python "
"interpreter, sidestepping the GIL. Threading would not help on CPU-bound "
"assembly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/distributed.rst:142
#: a5e5f4d9dccd4b50a68a90c4d24898cb
msgid ""
"**Ghost-node bookkeeping.** Each worker assembles a *local* "
"``SparseMatrix`` whose row/col are local DOF indices; the driver "
"translates them through ``orig_nid`` into global indices before stitching"
" the partial matrices together. The user-visible cost is a single GPU→CPU"
" copy per worker."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/distributed.rst:147
#: c2c5fe2997ee4ff8b35fa4557665af53
msgid ""
"**Per-card memory.** The benchmark's \"mem save\" column reports "
"``single_gpu_peak / max_per_card_peak`` — typically close to "
"``num_partitions`` for the assembly step itself, since each worker only "
"stores its own subdomain."
msgstr ""

